<refsect1 id="GnomeCanvasLine.description" role="desc">
<title role="desc.title">Description</title>

<para>
A canvas item for drawing lines. This canvas item uses a <link linkend="GnomeCanvasPoints"><type>GnomeCanvasPoints</type></link>
structure so one or multiple joined lined segments can be drawn with a single
<link linkend="GnomeCanvasLine"><type>GnomeCanvasLine</type></link> item.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="GnomeCanvasLine.details" role="details">
<title role="details.title">Details</title>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine-struct" role="struct">
<title>GnomeCanvasLine</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine-struct"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>typedef struct _GnomeCanvasLine GnomeCanvasLine;</programlisting>
<para>
This structure should not be accessed directly. Use the object's properties
for querying or changing its parameters.
</para></refsect2>

</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="GnomeCanvasLine.property-details" role="property_details">
<title role="property_details.title">Property Details</title>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--arrow-shape-a" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;arrow-shape-a&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--arrow-shape-a"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:arrow-shape-a</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;arrow-shape-a&quot;            <link linkend="gdouble">gdouble</link>               : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Distance from tip of arrowhead to center.
</para><para>Default value: 0</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--arrow-shape-b" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;arrow-shape-b&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--arrow-shape-b"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:arrow-shape-b</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;arrow-shape-b&quot;            <link linkend="gdouble">gdouble</link>               : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Distance from tip of arrowhead to trailing point, measured along shaft.
</para><para>Default value: 0</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--arrow-shape-c" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;arrow-shape-c&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--arrow-shape-c"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:arrow-shape-c</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;arrow-shape-c&quot;            <link linkend="gdouble">gdouble</link>               : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Distance of arrowhead trailing points from outside edge of shaft.
</para><para>Default value: 0</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--cap-style" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;cap-style&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--cap-style"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:cap-style</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;cap-style&quot;                <link linkend="GdkCapStyle">GdkCapStyle</link>           : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Determines how the ends of lines are drawn (the line cap style).
</para><para>Default value: GDK_CAP_BUTT</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-color" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;fill-color&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-color"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:fill-color</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;fill-color&quot;               <link linkend="gchar">gchar</link>*                : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
X color specification for line.
</para><para>Default value: NULL</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-color-gdk" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;fill-color-gdk&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-color-gdk"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:fill-color-gdk</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;fill-color-gdk&quot;           <link linkend="GdkColor">GdkColor</link>*             : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Pointer to an allocated GdkColor to draw the line with.
</para></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-color-rgba" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;fill-color-rgba&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-color-rgba"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:fill-color-rgba</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;fill-color-rgba&quot;          <link linkend="guint">guint</link>                 : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Line color with an alpha component (in the format 0xRRGGBBAA).
</para><para>Default value: 0</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-stipple" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;fill-stipple&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--fill-stipple"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:fill-stipple</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;fill-stipple&quot;             <link linkend="GdkDrawable">GdkDrawable</link>*          : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Stipple pattern for the line.
</para></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--first-arrowhead" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;first-arrowhead&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--first-arrowhead"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:first-arrowhead</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;first-arrowhead&quot;          <link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>              : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Specifies whether to draw an arrowhead on the first point of the line.
</para><para>Default value: FALSE</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--join-style" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;join-style&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--join-style"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:join-style</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;join-style&quot;               <link linkend="GdkJoinStyle">GdkJoinStyle</link>          : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Vertex join style for line segments (GDK_JOIN_MITER to join by
extending each line to meet at an angle, GDK_JOIN_ROUND to join by a
circular arc, and GDK_JOIN_BEVEL to join by a straight line which
makes an equal angle with each line).
</para><para>Default value: GDK_JOIN_MITER</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--last-arrowhead" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;last-arrowhead&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--last-arrowhead"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:last-arrowhead</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;last-arrowhead&quot;           <link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>              : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Specifies whether to draw an arrowhead on the last point of the line.
</para><para>Default value: FALSE</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--line-style" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;line-style&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--line-style"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:line-style</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;line-style&quot;               <link linkend="GdkLineStyle">GdkLineStyle</link>          : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Line dash style.
</para><para>Default value: GDK_LINE_SOLID</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--points" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;points&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--points"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:points</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;points&quot;                   <link linkend="GnomeCanvasPoints">GnomeCanvasPoints</link>*    : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Pointer to a <link linkend="GnomeCanvasPoints"><type>GnomeCanvasPoints</type></link> structure. This can be created by a
call to <link linkend="gnome-canvas-points-new"><function>gnome_canvas_points_new()</function></link>.
</para></refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--smooth" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;smooth&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--smooth"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:smooth</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;smooth&quot;                   <link linkend="gboolean">gboolean</link>              : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Specifies whether to smooth the line using parabolic splines.
</para><para>Default value: FALSE</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--spline-steps" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;spline-steps&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--spline-steps"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:spline-steps</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;spline-steps&quot;             <link linkend="guint">guint</link>                 : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Specifies the number of steps to use when rendering curves.
</para><para>Default value: 12</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--width-pixels" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;width-pixels&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--width-pixels"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:width-pixels</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;width-pixels&quot;             <link linkend="guint">guint</link>                 : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Width of the line in pixels.  The line width will not be scaled when
the canvas zoom factor changes.
</para><para>Default value: 0</para>
</refsect2>
<refsect2 id="GnomeCanvasLine--width-units" role="property"><title>The <literal>&quot;width-units&quot;</literal> property</title>
<indexterm zone="GnomeCanvasLine--width-units"><primary>GnomeCanvasLine:width-units</primary></indexterm>
<programlisting>  &quot;width-units&quot;              <link linkend="gdouble">gdouble</link>               : Read / Write</programlisting>
<para>
Width of the line in canvas units.  The line width will be scaled when
the canvas zoom factor changes.
</para><para>Allowed values: &gt;= 0</para>
<para>Default value: 0</para>
</refsect2>
</refsect1>




